Bring a large #pot{} of water to a boil with a large pinch of @salt{pinch}. Meanwhile, halve, peel, and dice the @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced). Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Finely chop the @parsley{1%bunch}(finely chopped). Trim and discard the bottom inch of the @asparagus{1%bunch}(trimmed), then cut into 1-inch pieces. Core, seed, and remove the white veins from the @green bell pepper{1}(cored and seeded). Cut into strips, then into 1/2-inch cubes. Cut the @broccoli florets{1}(cut into bite sized florets).

Fill a large #bowl{} with ice water. Add the broccoli to the boiling water for ~{4-5%minutes}, until bright green and crisp-tender. Remove from water with a #slotted spoon{} and reserve in the ice bath. Add the asparagus to the boiling water for ~{2-3%minutes}, until bright green and crisp-tender. Reserve in the ice bath with the broccoli. Keep the water boiling on the stove for the pasta later!

Heat 2 teaspoons @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Season the @chicken breasts{2} on both sides with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the chicken to the pan and cook ~{4-5%minutes} per side, until juices run clear when pierced. Set aside.

Add the @orecchiette pasta{6%ounce} to the boiling water and cook for ~{9-10%minutes}, until al dente. Reserve 1/2 cup pasta water, then drain.

Meanwhile, heat 1 teaspoon olive oil in the same pan over medium heat. Add the onion and bell pepper and cook for ~{6-8%minutes}, tossing, until softened. Add the garlic and @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} (or more if you like!) and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice the chicken against the grain, then add it to the pan along with the pasta, broccoli, asparagus, @sour cream{1/4%cup}, half the @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, half the parsley, and a splash of pasta water. Toss to combine, then season with salt and pepper to taste.

Serve sprinkled with remaining parsley and Parmesan and enjoy!

> Primavera is Italian for Spring, so naturally we've loaded up this pasta with plenty of
> spring veggies! We think orecchiette is the perfect vehicle for a creamy, cheesy sauce
> like this one. Spiced up with a little chili pepper heat, this pasta is bound to please!